txt.en: 'Who are you? What? Food already? Splendid!'
'Finally! It's been hours since I last ate!'
'Time to eat? Oh, I suppose I shouldn’t have had all those berries. …eh! There's always room for more.'
A weary mother has her hands full making a meal for her five children.
Told children to come and eat ([placeholder]/[placeholder])

'If ye're coming 'round looking for food, I haven't any for ye. No offence meant, but with five ravenous children there's not a bite left over for a stranger. But say, I could offer ye some coin if ye could help me out.\n\n'The children are afield playing and gathering or whatever it is they do that gets them covered with mud, burrs, and smelling like a dunghill. Will ye let them know 'tis time for a meal?'
'The children are all on their way? Lovely! A fine job you did! I do no' suppose ye would set aside yer adventuring ways for that of a nanny, eh? Hah hah, nor would I.\n\n'Well, ye have me thanks!'
Rosentyl Flutch has asked you to let her children know that it is time to eat.\n\nRosentyl's children can be found around Clegur.
'The children are scattered about Clegur. If ye could call them to the table, I would be able to get so much more done with my day!'
Tell children to come and eat ([placeholder]/[placeholder])
Rosentyl is in Clegur.\n\nYou should let Rosentyl know that you have told all of her children to come enjoy the meal she has cooked.
'Food's ready? All right! I will head back right away!'
'Oh, hullo. Yes, I suppose I can head home to sup.'
